# group1group2
group1 <- c(5.1, 4.9, 6.3, 5.8, 5.4, 5.0, 6.1)
group2 <- c(6.5, 7.2, 6.8, 7.0, 6.9, 7.3, 7.1)

# t.test()t
t_test_result <- t.test(group1, group2, var.equal = TRUE)

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = c("lightblue","lightpink")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Boxplot of Group 1 and Group 2", x = "Group", y = "Value")

# 
means <- c(mean(group1), mean(group2))
sds <- c(sd(group1), sd(group2))
bar_error <- barplot(means, 
        names.arg = c("group1","group2"), 
        col = c("lightblue", "lightgreen"), 
        main = "Mean Values of Group 1 and Group 2",
        xlab = "Groups", 
        ylab = "Mean Value",
        ylim = c(0, 8)
        )
# 
arrows(bar_error, means - sds, bar_error, means + sds, angle = 90, code = 3, length = 0.1, col = "red")
# 
text(bar_error, means + 0.1, labels = round(means, 2), pos = 2, cex = 0.8, col = "red")

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value)) +
